1
00:00:30,877 --> 00:00:33,903
We've started our descent.
Please put your seat back up.

2
00:00:34,081 --> 00:00:35,981
Let me help you.

3
00:00:37,484 --> 00:00:39,918
-Thanks.
-You're welcome.

4
00:00:43,657 --> 00:00:46,990
Sir, please put your seat back up.

5
00:01:20,260 --> 00:01:24,060
-Is your boyfriend meeting you?
-The old one or the young one?

6
00:01:24,665 --> 00:01:25,927
You?

7
00:01:26,099 --> 00:01:28,294
The married one
or the single one?

8
00:01:37,811 --> 00:01:40,245
Hello!
Are you coming to pick me up?

9
00:01:40,414 --> 00:01:42,575
<i>Xiang, I'm with a patient.</i>

10
00:01:43,016 --> 00:01:46,645
I've heard that one before,
Brian!

11
00:01:46,987 --> 00:01:51,321
<i>-Are you with your wife?
-I really am with a patient.</i>

12
00:01:52,125 --> 00:01:53,854
Okay, don't come, then.

13
00:01:54,061 --> 00:01:56,222
You don't ever have to pick me
up again.

14
00:01:57,597 --> 00:02:00,293
Let me call you back.

15
00:02:06,306 --> 00:02:08,137
-Sandy?
-Yeah?

16
00:02:08,308 --> 00:02:10,538
Sandy, my precious?

17
00:02:10,711 --> 00:02:14,010
Was your birthday trip fun?

18
00:02:14,181 --> 00:02:15,978
It was okay.

19
00:02:16,149 --> 00:02:20,882
Dad, our daughter's
going away.

20
00:02:21,388 --> 00:02:23,481
Say a few words.

21
00:02:25,659 --> 00:02:28,924
You're glued to that game,
Sandy.

22
00:02:29,262 --> 00:02:30,923
You'll go blind!

23
00:02:32,366 --> 00:02:33,628
Yeah, sure.

24
00:02:33,800 --> 00:02:36,496
-Look at this, Dad.
-Here's the luggage now.

25
00:02:36,670 --> 00:02:39,798
Let me know when you have time.

26
00:02:41,041 --> 00:02:44,477
Right, of course I will.

27
00:02:44,711 --> 00:02:47,703
No problem.

28
00:03:38,932 --> 00:03:41,992
Hi, is Shi Ge there?

29
00:03:42,335 --> 00:03:45,304
This is Xiao Jie.
I'm here in Taipei.

30
00:03:45,472 --> 00:03:47,770
Are you coming to pick me up?

31
00:03:49,743 --> 00:03:53,304
Hoping East Road.
But I've never been here before.

32
00:03:53,480 --> 00:03:56,244
What if I can't find it?

33
00:04:14,601 --> 00:04:16,228
<i>Hello?</i>

34
00:04:16,736 --> 00:04:19,500
Still mad at me, Xiang?

35
00:04:20,073 --> 00:04:22,974
<i>I was mixing for Gigi that day.
I couldn't get away.</i>

36
00:04:23,143 --> 00:04:26,044
I don't care if it was Gigi
or Madonna.

37
00:04:26,213 --> 00:04:28,443
I never want to see you again.

38
00:04:28,615 --> 00:04:30,082
<i>Why?</i>

39
00:04:30,584 --> 00:04:32,415
We're just not right
for each other.

40
00:04:32,586 --> 00:04:34,019
<i>Why?</i>

41
00:04:34,321 --> 00:04:37,688
Why what? Why always ''why''?

42
00:04:37,924 --> 00:04:40,518
<i>-I'm boarding now.
-Didn't you just land?</i>

43
00:04:41,962 --> 00:04:44,954
I know you did. I checked.
You just got back, didn't you?

44
00:04:46,132 --> 00:04:48,896
We need you here, Qi.

45
00:04:50,370 --> 00:04:52,031
Okay.

46
00:05:07,487 --> 00:05:10,388
Good morning, Mr. Jack!

47
00:05:10,590 --> 00:05:13,559
You're not up yet?

48
00:05:13,960 --> 00:05:16,394
But it's already 7 a.m.
in New York!

49
00:05:19,399 --> 00:05:21,458
I just came back from Malaysia.

50
00:05:21,635 --> 00:05:24,627
Wait a minute.

51
00:05:26,907 --> 00:05:29,273
Give it to me straight.

52
00:05:29,442 --> 00:05:32,138
Are you sleeping alone?

53
00:05:34,147 --> 00:05:36,377
We're not seeing each other.

54
00:05:36,550 --> 00:05:38,780
You can tell me the truth.

55
00:05:41,087 --> 00:05:45,319
Me? I sleep alone sometimes.

56
00:05:45,525 --> 00:05:51,361
Sometimes with someone.
Sometimes with lots of people.

57
00:05:52,666 --> 00:05:55,533
I have to when I'm
on the plane!

58
00:05:56,703 --> 00:05:59,365
I called because I was bored!

59
00:06:02,509 --> 00:06:05,876
How can I find a decent man
with all the flying?

60
00:06:07,347 --> 00:06:09,975
What else can I do?

61
00:06:10,884 --> 00:06:15,719
I'm not going to follow my mother
and teach piano!

62
00:06:15,922 --> 00:06:18,186
It hasn't gotten that bad yet.

63
00:06:18,391 --> 00:06:21,827
Never forget,
it was my mother who broke us up.

64
00:06:25,432 --> 00:06:29,664
Fortunately,
I didn't marry you then.

65
00:06:29,836 --> 00:06:32,532
It'd be tragic to be married
to a playboy like you.

66
00:06:33,573 --> 00:06:36,872
Would you really take care of me
in my old age?

67
00:06:38,912 --> 00:06:41,676
It's good to be home. I'm beat.

68
00:06:41,848 --> 00:06:44,180
Aren't you going to work?

69
00:06:47,287 --> 00:06:49,653
What's wrong with these lights?

70
00:06:49,856 --> 00:06:53,019
All alone with no one
to fix the lights for me.

71
00:07:18,151 --> 00:07:20,176
Help.

72
00:07:28,395 --> 00:07:32,627
<i>The Meteorology Center
reports that the earthquake...</i>

73
00:07:32,799 --> 00:07:35,734
<i>...was 5.0 on the Richter scale.</i>

74
00:07:35,902 --> 00:07:39,235
<i>Fires were reported in the Shilin
and Nangang Districts in Taipei.</i>

75
00:07:39,406 --> 00:07:44,036
<i>Minor injuries have been reported
and treated at the hospital.</i>

76
00:07:44,210 --> 00:07:49,614
<i>Districts in Taipei have reported
minor damages to buildings.</i>

77
00:07:49,783 --> 00:07:54,152
<i>Evaluations are being done to
determine the extent of damages.</i>

78
00:07:54,320 --> 00:07:57,517
<i>The weather bureau has issued
an aftershock warning...</i>

79
00:07:57,724 --> 00:08:02,093
<i>...for the next few days. How's
everyone feeling after the quake?</i>

80
00:08:02,262 --> 00:08:04,730
<i>Let's go to some live interviews.</i>

81
00:08:04,931 --> 00:08:07,263
<i>Why are you still on the street?</i>

82
00:08:07,901 --> 00:08:12,031
<i>-I came out with my girlfriend.
-What about aftershocks?</i>

83
00:08:12,205 --> 00:08:13,900
Xiang, are you okay?

84
00:08:15,275 --> 00:08:16,799
Please open the door!

85
00:08:21,581 --> 00:08:23,014
Xiang!

86
00:08:23,483 --> 00:08:25,348
Are you there?

87
00:08:25,585 --> 00:08:27,280
Let me in!

88
00:08:29,723 --> 00:08:32,351
Is someone with you?

89
00:08:34,728 --> 00:08:37,128
Open up!

90
00:08:38,498 --> 00:08:40,125
Xiang!

91
00:08:42,168 --> 00:08:43,863
Open the door!

92
00:08:53,947 --> 00:08:55,209
<i>-Hello?
-Miss Ku...</i>

93
00:08:55,381 --> 00:08:58,350
<i>...your windshield's been smashed.
Shall I call the police?</i>

94
00:08:58,518 --> 00:09:00,383
No, ignore him.

95
00:09:18,037 --> 00:09:19,299
Hello?

96
00:09:19,472 --> 00:09:22,737
<i>-I can come over pretty soon.
-No, don't.</i>

97
00:09:22,909 --> 00:09:24,342
-Brian.
-Meet me at Pixel.

98
00:09:24,511 --> 00:09:26,342
<i>-No.
-Brian.</i>

99
00:09:26,513 --> 00:09:28,708
-I'll wait for you.
-My fish are everywhere.

100
00:09:28,882 --> 00:09:30,440
Thank God none died.

101
00:09:57,677 --> 00:09:59,167
Xiang!

102
00:10:00,547 --> 00:10:03,482
Xiang! What are you doing?

103
00:10:03,650 --> 00:10:05,948
-Why do you treat me like this?
-Let go of me!

104
00:10:06,119 --> 00:10:08,587
-Why didn't you open the door?
-I have a date.

105
00:10:08,755 --> 00:10:10,950
Don't be like this.

106
00:10:14,761 --> 00:10:17,457
Let's talk, okay?

107
00:10:17,630 --> 00:10:19,257
Let go of me first.

108
00:10:21,467 --> 00:10:23,992
I left work early
just to pick you up.

109
00:10:24,170 --> 00:10:27,662
-Why didn't you wait for me?
-Why did you smash my car?

110
00:10:27,841 --> 00:10:29,968
Who are you to tell me
what to do?

111
00:10:30,510 --> 00:10:34,844
You can't treat people like this.
You come and go as you like.

112
00:10:35,014 --> 00:10:38,506
That's me! That's my life.

113
00:10:42,255 --> 00:10:46,021
-Don't be like this. Forgive me.
-Let go of me.

114
00:10:48,294 --> 00:10:50,353
You're so immature.

115
00:10:52,031 --> 00:10:54,465
You wouldn't love me
if I were mature.

116
00:10:55,969 --> 00:10:58,199
Don't take me for a fool.

117
00:11:15,722 --> 00:11:18,350
Don't leave me.

118
00:11:34,707 --> 00:11:36,265
What's wrong?

119
00:11:37,877 --> 00:11:41,335
Xiang, what's wrong?

120
00:11:55,595 --> 00:11:57,392
Marry me?

121
00:12:07,073 --> 00:12:08,540
Okay?

122
00:12:12,679 --> 00:12:15,546
Why do you always avoid
the subject?

123
00:12:17,717 --> 00:12:21,653
Look me in the eyes.
Look at me!

124
00:12:22,989 --> 00:12:24,684
Marry me, will you?

125
00:12:29,028 --> 00:12:31,690
Give me a straight answer.

126
00:12:31,931 --> 00:12:34,161
Or you won't see me again.

127
00:12:35,368 --> 00:12:37,268
Are you threatening me?

128
00:12:37,770 --> 00:12:42,707
-I don't like being threatened.
-Yes! I'm threatening you.

129
00:12:43,843 --> 00:12:46,334
Don't ask me to pick you up.

130
00:12:46,512 --> 00:12:51,142
Don't call me when you're lonely.
I mean it.

131
00:12:51,417 --> 00:12:53,442
You're being childish again.

132
00:12:53,619 --> 00:12:57,680
Don't say that.

133
00:12:58,157 --> 00:13:00,489
Will you marry me?

134
00:13:01,160 --> 00:13:02,991
Okay?

135
00:13:03,496 --> 00:13:04,986
-No.
-Marry me!

136
00:13:05,198 --> 00:13:08,258
-No.
-Marry me!

137
00:13:08,434 --> 00:13:10,061
-No!
-Marry me!

138
00:13:10,236 --> 00:13:11,931
Yes. No.

139
00:14:06,659 --> 00:14:08,126
Thank you.

140
00:14:24,010 --> 00:14:28,242
<i>Brian Sun! If you have the balls,
come face me!</i>

141
00:15:39,652 --> 00:15:42,917
Here she is! I hear the sound
of money at my door!

142
00:15:43,089 --> 00:15:48,493
-You'll call us twins? No way!
-You'll be twins if I say so.

143
00:15:48,661 --> 00:15:50,390
This place was hard to find.

144
00:15:50,563 --> 00:15:52,895
Yes, it's a little out of the way.

145
00:15:53,065 --> 00:15:56,034
-This is Jie from Singapore.
-Malaysia.

146
00:15:56,202 --> 00:16:00,400
Right, Malaysia.
This is Tong from Hong Kong.

147
00:16:00,606 --> 00:16:02,198
Hi.

148
00:16:02,475 --> 00:16:05,035
What's with the handshake?

149
00:16:05,211 --> 00:16:07,008
Rude!

150
00:16:07,180 --> 00:16:09,705
Sit!

151
00:16:09,949 --> 00:16:12,247
Let me see you together.

152
00:16:21,627 --> 00:16:23,390
Very little resemblance indeed.

153
00:16:24,197 --> 00:16:29,100
No matter. I'll still present you
as twin sisters.

154
00:16:29,268 --> 00:16:33,329
Audiences want
satisfaction nowadays.

155
00:16:33,506 --> 00:16:39,911
lmagine a pair
of singing and dancing twins...

156
00:16:40,079 --> 00:16:42,980
...who can maybe do
some magic tricks.

157
00:16:43,149 --> 00:16:46,141
People will just fall over
themselves.

158
00:16:46,986 --> 00:16:49,147
I'm telling you!

159
00:16:49,322 --> 00:16:52,314
This is a world
without boundaries.

160
00:16:52,491 --> 00:16:54,425
You're from
two different places.

161
00:16:54,594 --> 00:16:56,892
Your union will be a symbol...

162
00:16:57,063 --> 00:17:01,762
...of the global village.

163
00:17:03,002 --> 00:17:04,970
Who's hot now?

164
00:17:05,137 --> 00:17:07,037
-F4
-Yes.

165
00:17:07,306 --> 00:17:12,209
And there is Yang Yang.

166
00:17:12,378 --> 00:17:17,145
They all have a common appeal.
They make people smile.

167
00:17:17,316 --> 00:17:20,046
They have that
feel-good quality.

168
00:17:20,386 --> 00:17:26,120
Whether you're from Hong Kong,
Taiwan or anywhere else...

169
00:17:26,626 --> 00:17:29,459
...everyone just needs
some simple fun.

170
00:17:29,629 --> 00:17:30,891
Where are you staying?

171
00:17:31,063 --> 00:17:32,928
If their idols
make them feel good....

172
00:17:33,099 --> 00:17:35,465
She doesn't even
have a place to stay!

173
00:17:35,635 --> 00:17:38,365
It doesn't matter,
they can't sing or dance.

174
00:17:38,904 --> 00:17:41,498
Sorry about that.

175
00:17:42,074 --> 00:17:45,237
-That's okay, I got it.
-Here, let me help.

176
00:17:45,411 --> 00:17:48,380
-I got it.
-Let me help you.

177
00:17:48,547 --> 00:17:50,412
-It's heavy.
-It's okay.

178
00:17:50,583 --> 00:17:52,244
You've got it?

179
00:17:53,352 --> 00:17:57,686
-Where's the hotel?
-Not far. Let's take the bus.

180
00:18:03,129 --> 00:18:05,063
Sit anywhere.

181
00:18:19,412 --> 00:18:20,709
Can I use your closet?

182
00:18:21,647 --> 00:18:23,774
-Sure, why not?
-Thanks.

183
00:18:24,216 --> 00:18:26,480
I've never been to Malaysia.

184
00:18:27,420 --> 00:18:29,888
I'm from Alor Setar.

185
00:18:30,056 --> 00:18:32,354
It's small but beautiful.

186
00:18:33,225 --> 00:18:35,250
How come you speak Cantonese?

187
00:18:35,461 --> 00:18:37,019
I learned it by watching movies.

188
00:18:37,229 --> 00:18:41,063
We have lots of Cantonese movies
and a lot of Canto-pop music.

189
00:18:42,635 --> 00:18:44,364
What time
are our lessons tomorrow?

190
00:18:51,944 --> 00:18:53,809
Don't we have to learn
lots of things?

191
00:18:53,979 --> 00:18:57,073
-Singing. Dancing.
-Yeah.

192
00:18:57,249 --> 00:18:58,876
I'm really nervous.

193
00:19:06,092 --> 00:19:08,322
Forget about it. It'll dry.

194
00:19:09,528 --> 00:19:11,496
Let me clean it up anyway.

195
00:19:16,168 --> 00:19:18,932
-What's happening?
-What?

196
00:19:19,372 --> 00:19:22,364
-What's going on?
-Earthquake.

197
00:20:01,347 --> 00:20:04,612
Earthquake! Are you scared?

198
00:20:13,259 --> 00:20:14,692
Thank you for the interview.

199
00:20:14,860 --> 00:20:16,725
Excuse me. This lady.
May I ask...?

200
00:20:16,896 --> 00:20:20,093
Excuse me, madam.
Madam, may l...?

201
00:20:20,266 --> 00:20:22,257
I'm sorry. I know nothing.

202
00:20:22,435 --> 00:20:26,337
Another earthquake!
What do you feel?

203
00:20:26,906 --> 00:20:30,865
Can I ask a question? It'll
just take a couple of minutes.

204
00:20:31,143 --> 00:20:33,202
Please. It's just an interview.

205
00:20:40,953 --> 00:20:42,921
Jie! We're on TV!

206
00:20:43,088 --> 00:20:44,646
What?

207
00:20:50,996 --> 00:20:54,295
I want to record it for my mother.
I have a digital video camera.

208
00:20:54,467 --> 00:20:56,264
<i>No earthquakes in Hong Kong,
right?</i>

209
00:20:56,435 --> 00:21:00,428
<i>No, but we have typhoons.</i>

210
00:21:01,273 --> 00:21:05,232
<i>-Yes, typhoons.
-So this is your first earthquake?</i>

211
00:21:05,578 --> 00:21:07,842
<i>Yes, it was pretty scary.</i>

212
00:21:08,013 --> 00:21:10,345
<i>We don't have earthquakes
in Malaysia.</i>

213
00:21:10,516 --> 00:21:13,246
<i>At first I was scared,
but I'm okay now.</i>

214
00:21:20,192 --> 00:21:23,161
Mom, I was on TV.

215
00:21:23,329 --> 00:21:26,196
<i>-I taped it for you.
-Are you okay?</i>

216
00:21:26,365 --> 00:21:29,801
<i>-Everything is fine. How are you?
-I'm worried about you over there.</i>

217
00:21:29,969 --> 00:21:32,699
<i>-I'm living with a girl.
-Take care of yourself.</i>

218
00:21:32,872 --> 00:21:36,501
<i>We're worried sick
about you being away.</i>

219
00:21:36,675 --> 00:21:41,203
<i>Dad is really upset.
I'm putting in a good word for you.</i>

220
00:21:41,380 --> 00:21:43,439
I know.

221
00:21:43,749 --> 00:21:45,182
<i>Please come home soon....</i>

222
00:21:45,351 --> 00:21:47,842
This call is expensive.
I must go.

223
00:21:48,020 --> 00:21:51,012
<i>-Keep in touch!
-Okay.</i>

224
00:21:59,798 --> 00:22:03,928
The flowers. Oh, my God!

225
00:22:05,738 --> 00:22:08,571
Nothing seems to be broken.

226
00:22:24,757 --> 00:22:27,783
Hey! I was terrified last night.

227
00:22:27,993 --> 00:22:31,759
I was on the subway,
and it felt like a roller coaster.

228
00:22:31,931 --> 00:22:33,660
Okay, let's get on and clean up.

229
00:22:33,832 --> 00:22:38,235
-At least nothing's broken.
-Yeah, clean them up.

230
00:22:38,404 --> 00:22:39,837
Yes.

231
00:22:41,340 --> 00:22:44,571
Mrs. Zhao, I need the day off.
My father had a heart attack.

232
00:22:44,743 --> 00:22:46,677
I need to go to the hospital.

233
00:22:47,913 --> 00:22:50,313
-Add some more of these.
-Okay.

234
00:22:50,482 --> 00:22:52,712
Our glass door was shattered.

235
00:22:52,885 --> 00:22:54,876
We were pretty lucky here.

236
00:22:55,054 --> 00:22:57,022
-Just a few broken pots.
-I'll say.

237
00:22:57,189 --> 00:23:00,784
-Hello. Love Home Florist.
-With some more white daisies.

238
00:23:02,428 --> 00:23:03,952
What's the matter?

239
00:23:04,163 --> 00:23:07,462
My mother fell from a window.

240
00:23:07,633 --> 00:23:09,760
-What? Which floor was she on?
-The second.

241
00:23:09,935 --> 00:23:12,631
-I'm going to the hospital.
-The second isn't too bad.

242
00:23:12,805 --> 00:23:16,571
Don't worry. Will you be back?
She won't call.

243
00:23:16,742 --> 00:23:18,801
Hello! Love Home Hospital.

244
00:23:20,512 --> 00:23:22,104
Love Home Florist.

245
00:23:22,715 --> 00:23:26,082
The flowers will be delivered
on time.

246
00:24:06,458 --> 00:24:10,053
What are you doing?
This street's one-way!

247
00:24:10,262 --> 00:24:12,730
Sorry, sorry.

248
00:24:13,699 --> 00:24:17,100
Patience, patience.

249
00:24:22,641 --> 00:24:25,508
-Yes?
-For Mr. and Mrs. Zhao.

250
00:24:25,678 --> 00:24:27,771
-Yes.
-Anniversary.

251
00:24:27,946 --> 00:24:29,345
Okay, thank you.

252
00:24:29,515 --> 00:24:33,042
-Where shall I put these?
-Over there.

253
00:25:20,933 --> 00:25:24,061
-Twelve, 1 1 , 1 0, 9...
-Twelve, 1 1 , 1 0, 9...

254
00:25:24,403 --> 00:25:28,362
