255
00:25:58,237 --> 00:26:01,001
-Hey!
-What?

256
00:26:01,173 --> 00:26:02,504
-That's my idol!
-Who?

257
00:26:02,674 --> 00:26:04,073
-Qi Yu.
-Who's Qi Yu?

258
00:26:04,243 --> 00:26:07,076
She sings ''Olive Tree''
and ''Walk in the Rain.''

259
00:26:07,913 --> 00:26:10,177
I know her!
Let's get an autograph.

260
00:26:10,349 --> 00:26:13,284
-Where's my notebook?
-Got any paper?

261
00:26:14,086 --> 00:26:16,384
Got it. Here, here.

262
00:26:19,258 --> 00:26:21,920
Qi Yu. Miss Qi Yu.

263
00:26:22,127 --> 00:26:24,687
-Hi!
-Could I get your autograph?

264
00:26:25,898 --> 00:26:28,423
-I love your music.
-Me too!

265
00:26:28,600 --> 00:26:30,659
The first album I bought
was yours.

266
00:26:30,836 --> 00:26:35,170
-Really?
-Yes. Thank you.

267
00:26:47,653 --> 00:26:51,680
-He looks cheesy.
-I think he's good-looking.

268
00:26:51,890 --> 00:26:53,915
-That's my type.
-A real hunk.

269
00:26:54,126 --> 00:26:57,323
It's not how they look.

270
00:26:57,496 --> 00:26:58,963
Take Shi Ge.

271
00:26:59,164 --> 00:27:02,190
It's what's inside that counts.

272
00:27:02,367 --> 00:27:04,699
So you know what's inside
Shi Ge?

273
00:27:04,870 --> 00:27:09,136
-Real talent.
-Crazy girls.

274
00:27:13,245 --> 00:27:15,839
The guys I like don't like me.

275
00:27:16,014 --> 00:27:18,039
Those I don't like
always go for me.

276
00:27:18,217 --> 00:27:20,811
When I'm famous,
I'll marry Tony Leung.

277
00:27:20,986 --> 00:27:22,351
He'll leave his girlfriend?

278
00:27:22,521 --> 00:27:25,854
-I am younger than her.
-He'll be old by then.

279
00:27:26,058 --> 00:27:28,526
Doesn't matter,
I still love him.

280
00:27:29,661 --> 00:27:32,391
Do you have a girlfriend,
Shi Ge?

281
00:27:32,564 --> 00:27:35,328
What's it to you? Of course.

282
00:27:38,437 --> 00:27:40,098
Is she from Hong Kong?

283
00:27:40,439 --> 00:27:42,339
Is she a pop star?

284
00:27:42,774 --> 00:27:46,471
-She's an ordinary person.
-Do we know her?

285
00:27:47,045 --> 00:27:48,603
No, she's not famous.

286
00:27:48,780 --> 00:27:52,739
-Then how do you know her?
-How?

287
00:27:53,185 --> 00:27:56,712
She has a beautiful voice.

288
00:27:56,889 --> 00:27:59,380
She's pretty, with long hair.

289
00:28:00,893 --> 00:28:05,296
I wrote songs for her,
but it's no good.

290
00:28:06,331 --> 00:28:08,060
She's married,
so, what's the point?

291
00:28:08,233 --> 00:28:10,497
Wow, he's in love!

292
00:28:11,036 --> 00:28:14,802
You guys are crazy.

293
00:28:14,973 --> 00:28:17,567
Get out. You're distracting me.

294
00:28:17,743 --> 00:28:22,237
-When do we start working?
-We can't start without a song.

295
00:28:22,414 --> 00:28:26,510
I'm writing one.
Get out and practice.

296
00:28:26,685 --> 00:28:30,314
-Practice, practice, practice.
-Go away.

297
00:28:30,522 --> 00:28:32,490
We're off to practice.

298
00:28:40,599 --> 00:28:43,261
I have five brothers and sisters.
I'm the oldest.

299
00:28:43,435 --> 00:28:45,369
My father works
on a rubber plantation.

300
00:28:45,537 --> 00:28:47,402
My mother stays home
and cares for us.

301
00:28:47,773 --> 00:28:50,936
My dad and I support
the family...

302
00:28:52,144 --> 00:28:54,305
...so this is my last chance.

303
00:28:54,479 --> 00:28:58,882
If this doesn't work, I'll have
to go back to a boring job.

304
00:28:59,051 --> 00:29:02,885
A clerk, maybe, or a salesgirl.

305
00:29:03,055 --> 00:29:05,615
Do you really love
to sing and dance?

306
00:29:05,824 --> 00:29:07,451
I love singing the most.

307
00:29:07,659 --> 00:29:11,652
At least it's something
you want to do.

308
00:29:12,764 --> 00:29:14,391
What about you?

309
00:29:14,967 --> 00:29:17,197
Isn't there something
you want to do?

310
00:29:17,636 --> 00:29:19,001
Me?

311
00:29:25,577 --> 00:29:28,171
I didn't want to tell you...

312
00:29:29,114 --> 00:29:31,412
...but suddenly
I feel like saying it.

313
00:29:32,217 --> 00:29:34,151
Are you listening?

314
00:29:38,323 --> 00:29:41,486
My mother is having an affair.

315
00:29:44,863 --> 00:29:49,766
I need to know what he's like
and how he could...

316
00:29:50,335 --> 00:29:54,431
...turn my mother away from my dad.

317
00:29:59,044 --> 00:30:01,979
-Have you ever been in love?
-Me?

318
00:30:03,749 --> 00:30:05,808
I had a boyfriend once.

319
00:30:06,284 --> 00:30:10,516
I don't think it was love.

320
00:30:10,756 --> 00:30:13,088
Isn't it the same thing?

321
00:30:13,325 --> 00:30:17,557
How is it different? If you
want to be with him, it's love.

322
00:30:18,030 --> 00:30:20,498
Why would you dump someone
you like?

323
00:30:25,270 --> 00:30:27,033
Why didn't you come out
that day?

324
00:30:28,073 --> 00:30:31,406
You didn't even answer my call.
I waited for you downstairs.

325
00:30:34,212 --> 00:30:36,806
I know you were home.

326
00:30:43,922 --> 00:30:46,413
Are you mad at me?

327
00:30:52,197 --> 00:30:54,290
Is your wife away on business?

328
00:30:58,236 --> 00:30:59,863
She's in Beijing.

329
00:31:04,409 --> 00:31:07,173
I thought we agreed
not to complain.

330
00:31:14,286 --> 00:31:15,878
Sorry.

331
00:31:22,394 --> 00:31:24,453
I'm flying to Europe this time.

332
00:31:25,897 --> 00:31:28,388
Let's think about this thing
between us.

333
00:31:30,702 --> 00:31:33,637
We need to make up our minds.

334
00:31:37,776 --> 00:31:39,869
You said there'd be
no strings attached.

335
00:31:40,345 --> 00:31:43,508
I am not attaching strings.

336
00:31:45,250 --> 00:31:50,449
I'm just not sure
I love you anymore.

337
00:31:56,161 --> 00:31:58,129
I have to go.

338
00:32:17,782 --> 00:32:19,909
We're all old friends.

339
00:32:20,085 --> 00:32:22,576
I really don't know
how to do this.

340
00:32:23,121 --> 00:32:27,421
I hope you can cool down
for a while and reconsider.

341
00:32:30,562 --> 00:32:32,860
Thank you for the advice.

342
00:32:41,373 --> 00:32:46,743
Lily, I didn't want a divorce.

343
00:32:50,448 --> 00:32:51,779
Your keys!

344
00:33:39,264 --> 00:33:43,564
Mommy, why do you
want a divorce?

345
00:33:46,471 --> 00:33:49,634
You'll understand
when you get older.

346
00:33:51,610 --> 00:33:53,544
Men can't be relied upon.

347
00:33:53,712 --> 00:33:55,873
We can get by just fine
without them.

348
00:33:56,047 --> 00:33:57,537
Do you have any savings?

349
00:33:57,849 --> 00:34:01,410
Don't forget about alimony.

350
00:34:01,586 --> 00:34:04,111
It's hard to find someone
at 40-something.

351
00:34:04,322 --> 00:34:07,780
When you do, you don't want them.

352
00:34:08,193 --> 00:34:09,717
Why not?

353
00:34:12,230 --> 00:34:13,891
If he's good, then why not?

354
00:34:19,704 --> 00:34:21,831
Bottoms up, down in one!

355
00:34:22,007 --> 00:34:26,376
Peter. Peter! One, 2, 3!

356
00:35:48,827 --> 00:35:51,295
Time to eat!

357
00:35:53,331 --> 00:35:55,026
Time to eat.

358
00:35:58,703 --> 00:36:00,568
Are you feeling better today?

359
00:36:08,546 --> 00:36:10,776
Linda, Grandma's winning!

360
00:36:10,949 --> 00:36:12,644
You bet.

361
00:36:15,420 --> 00:36:18,412
You can talk to her.

362
00:36:18,590 --> 00:36:20,649
She likes being talked to.

363
00:36:20,859 --> 00:36:22,258
She can hear you.

364
00:36:22,427 --> 00:36:25,453
Try reading the newspaper
to her.

365
00:36:25,663 --> 00:36:27,187
She likes that.

366
00:36:27,399 --> 00:36:29,162
She looks just fine.

