00:40:47,759 --> 00:40:49,989
I am dying.

402
00:40:52,497 --> 00:40:55,557
No one will care if I'm dead.

403
00:40:57,802 --> 00:41:01,238
I am going to die.

404
00:41:07,145 --> 00:41:09,045
I am dead.

405
00:41:13,551 --> 00:41:16,952
I'll marry the next guy
who knocks.

406
00:42:13,144 --> 00:42:16,978
Lots of people
are interested in your piano.

407
00:42:17,148 --> 00:42:21,050
-Are you really going to sell it?
-I want to sell everything.

408
00:42:21,219 --> 00:42:23,744
I want to sell myself too.

409
00:42:24,155 --> 00:42:29,252
This guy is looking for a piano
as a gift for his daughter.

410
00:42:29,460 --> 00:42:33,954
Whatever. If my mother found out,
she'd turn over in her grave.

411
00:42:34,165 --> 00:42:36,065
-Show me that one.
-Okay.

412
00:42:36,234 --> 00:42:38,725
-That one.
-This one?

413
00:42:42,206 --> 00:42:45,903
They're all black.
Going to a funeral?

414
00:42:46,644 --> 00:42:48,111
This one?

415
00:42:48,312 --> 00:42:50,906
No, that one.

416
00:42:51,249 --> 00:42:55,310
Which one?
Are you going to Ying's wedding?

417
00:42:57,655 --> 00:43:00,852
It's not me getting married.
Why bother?

418
00:43:07,632 --> 00:43:13,901
So expensive.
I can't wear them all.

419
00:43:30,855 --> 00:43:32,254
Hi.

420
00:43:33,357 --> 00:43:37,453
I'm packing.
I'm about to leave.

421
00:43:39,030 --> 00:43:42,966
Okay, get on with your surgery.
Bye.

422
00:43:52,243 --> 00:43:56,577
Hey, Qi, I'm packing.

423
00:43:57,481 --> 00:43:59,278
I'm about to leave.

424
00:43:59,984 --> 00:44:03,545
Get on with your
recording session. Bye.

425
00:44:07,892 --> 00:44:11,623
Hello, Jack. I'm packing.

426
00:44:11,796 --> 00:44:13,559
I'm about to leave.

427
00:44:13,731 --> 00:44:15,631
Shit!

428
00:44:24,075 --> 00:44:26,839
Why did you buy a tape recorder?

429
00:44:28,079 --> 00:44:30,309
I want to record my own stuff.

430
00:44:30,481 --> 00:44:34,383
Maybe a new song, a phrase...

431
00:44:34,552 --> 00:44:38,955
...the sounds of Taipei
and your voice babbling.

432
00:44:39,924 --> 00:44:42,518
This is my 20th day in Taipei.
Taipei's a big city.

433
00:44:42,727 --> 00:44:46,219
-What are you saying?
-Quiet! Don't talk behind my back.

434
00:44:46,430 --> 00:44:49,957
I have a fat, ugly friend,
and she babbles on every day.

435
00:44:50,134 --> 00:44:52,432
How dare you say I'm ugly!

436
00:44:52,603 --> 00:44:55,367
I'm babbling, not ugly.

437
00:44:56,407 --> 00:44:58,705
She does love to talk.

438
00:44:59,610 --> 00:45:01,635
I'm really happy.

439
00:45:01,812 --> 00:45:04,372
So no problem.
I'll just wait.

440
00:45:04,548 --> 00:45:07,346
We haven't started training,
let alone performing.

441
00:45:07,518 --> 00:45:11,682
-What are you saying?
-I'm badmouthing you!

442
00:45:44,188 --> 00:45:46,520
Have you ever kissed a girl?

443
00:45:47,925 --> 00:45:49,358
Have you?

444
00:45:49,894 --> 00:45:52,863
-I haven't!
-Me neither.

445
00:45:53,130 --> 00:45:55,894
In my school,
lots of girls like girls.

446
00:45:56,067 --> 00:45:58,092
Same here.

447
00:46:00,571 --> 00:46:04,598
Do all Malaysian girls
sleep in their bras?

448
00:46:04,775 --> 00:46:07,938
You! So, what do you call this?

449
00:46:10,214 --> 00:46:13,081
Why are you so scared when l...?

450
00:47:18,949 --> 00:47:21,747
How do you know those old songs?

451
00:47:22,586 --> 00:47:24,554
I learned them from my mother.

452
00:47:24,722 --> 00:47:27,953
She knows a lot of old songs.

453
00:47:28,159 --> 00:47:30,218
She has a great voice.

454
00:47:30,428 --> 00:47:32,020
You don't know these songs?

455
00:49:55,539 --> 00:49:57,200
Why am I here?

456
00:50:00,277 --> 00:50:02,541
What am I looking for?

457
00:50:17,094 --> 00:50:19,255
Oh, my God!

458
00:50:27,137 --> 00:50:30,504
So the long weekend's coming.
Any plans?

459
00:50:30,674 --> 00:50:32,403
Maybe the hot springs
with my man.

460
00:50:32,576 --> 00:50:34,976
-Great!
-We're going to the lake.

461
00:50:35,145 --> 00:50:39,138
-Really? Look, how's this?
-Not bad at all.

462
00:50:39,316 --> 00:50:41,716
-Okay, that's decided, then.
-Thanks.

463
00:50:41,885 --> 00:50:45,582
Guess what! I'm going to the
East Coast with my boyfriend.

464
00:50:45,789 --> 00:50:49,190
-I'm really looking forward to it!
-Bring me back a souvenir.

465
00:50:49,360 --> 00:50:51,828
-Me too.
-Do these go together?

466
00:50:51,996 --> 00:50:53,759
Sure! Let's see
how to arrange them.

467
00:50:53,931 --> 00:50:56,365
Where are you
and your husband going?

468
00:51:01,705 --> 00:51:05,300
James? This is Lily.

469
00:51:05,909 --> 00:51:09,777
You're still here! I figured
you'd be gone for the weekend.

470
00:51:10,581 --> 00:51:14,449
What? You're in Bangkok! Sorry!

471
00:51:14,618 --> 00:51:16,848
Hello. Is Mr. Wu there?

472
00:51:17,321 --> 00:51:18,982
This is....

473
00:51:19,423 --> 00:51:21,050
Who's this?

474
00:51:21,759 --> 00:51:26,526
Oh! Mrs. Wu.
Please tell him...

475
00:51:26,697 --> 00:51:30,326
...Ms. Shi called
from Citibank.

476
00:51:30,501 --> 00:51:33,834
Hi, Fred. This is Lily.

477
00:51:34,872 --> 00:51:36,533
Hello. Lu Yi-zheng.

478
00:51:36,707 --> 00:51:38,572
We were in elementary school
together.

479
00:51:38,742 --> 00:51:42,234
Lily Shi.
Are you free this weekend?

480
00:51:42,413 --> 00:51:44,404
Hello. Mr. Wang.

481
00:51:44,948 --> 00:51:50,011
Mr. Wang,
can you show me some apartments?

482
00:51:51,689 --> 00:51:53,520
You've changed jobs?

483
00:51:54,958 --> 00:51:57,984
May I ask what you're doing now?

484
00:51:59,697 --> 00:52:01,528
You're teaching tennis?

485
00:52:02,099 --> 00:52:04,329
You're teaching tennis.

486
00:52:05,969 --> 00:52:08,301
Tennis. Well, that's fine too.

487
00:52:08,605 --> 00:52:10,630
Let's start. Watch the ball.

488
00:52:12,009 --> 00:52:13,567
It's all right. Again.

489
00:52:17,981 --> 00:52:20,882
This is tennis, not dodge ball.

490
00:52:21,051 --> 00:52:23,679
Hit the ball,
don't hide from it.

491
00:52:23,854 --> 00:52:26,414
Hold the racket a little lower.

492
00:52:26,623 --> 00:52:29,820
Turn the handle back a little.
Hold tight.

493
00:52:30,027 --> 00:52:32,018
You'll gain more strength.

494
00:52:32,229 --> 00:52:36,996
Swing like this.
Swing through your shoulder.

495
00:52:37,167 --> 00:52:41,069
Same with your backhand.
Follow through smoothly.

496
00:52:41,271 --> 00:52:43,068
What's with the backhand?

497
00:52:43,240 --> 00:52:47,870
Grip tight with both hands. Stare
in the direction of the ball.

498
00:52:48,045 --> 00:52:51,014
Swing back through
your shoulder.

499
00:52:51,181 --> 00:52:53,240
Loosen up the shoulder a bit.

500
00:52:53,417 --> 00:52:55,851
-Look at the ball. Try this.
-Okay.

501
00:52:57,921 --> 00:52:59,513
Good.

502
00:52:59,823 --> 00:53:02,223
-Right?
-Look at the ball, not at me.

503
00:53:05,396 --> 00:53:07,227
Good, good!

504
00:53:31,455 --> 00:53:34,947
Hey, you don't look your age.

505
00:53:43,700 --> 00:53:45,895
Go, go, go.

506
00:53:49,239 --> 00:53:51,207
Move both your hands. Backhand.

507
00:53:53,076 --> 00:53:55,408
Forehand. To the front.

508
00:54:00,484 --> 00:54:03,612
Lily, come on.

509
00:54:06,123 --> 00:54:08,318
Are you doing okay?

510
00:54:18,802 --> 00:54:22,329
Lily, get up. Exercise time.

511
00:54:22,506 --> 00:54:24,940
Hurry! Wake up. Wake up.

512
00:54:25,108 --> 00:54:28,544
Get up and exercise.

513
00:54:28,712 --> 00:54:30,270
Come on!

514
00:54:32,015 --> 00:54:35,451
Off the bed. Come on!

515
00:54:35,853 --> 00:54:38,344
Move, move. Come on!

516
00:54:43,794 --> 00:54:45,318
Come on! Come on!

517
00:54:51,034 --> 00:54:53,002
-What's wrong?
-Nothing.

518
00:54:53,170 --> 00:54:57,368
Up, up! You're fine!
Come on. Almost there.

519
00:55:51,428 --> 00:55:53,225
Lily, my dear.

520
00:55:53,397 --> 00:55:56,161
No more, no more. I beg you.

521
00:55:56,333 --> 00:55:58,460
The more you resist
the more excited I get.

522
00:55:58,635 --> 00:56:02,366
Please, I really can't.

523
00:56:02,539 --> 00:56:04,837
-Lily! Come on.
-I'm begging you.

524
00:56:05,008 --> 00:56:07,476
Really, no more.

525
00:56:08,779 --> 00:56:10,679
No more.

526
00:56:12,015 --> 00:56:13,710
Lily.

527
00:56:18,388 --> 00:56:22,449
-Lily, come on. Don't run!
-I really can't!

528
00:56:34,304 --> 00:56:38,570
You won't find twin girls
in Taiwan...

529
00:56:38,742 --> 00:56:42,508
-...half as talented as mine.
-No kidding?

530
00:56:42,679 --> 00:56:46,979
The big labels approached me,
but I'm holding back.

531
00:56:47,150 --> 00:56:51,348
The majors, you name it.
I'm not doing business with them.

532
00:56:51,521 --> 00:56:54,081
Why's that?

533
00:56:54,291 --> 00:56:55,690
Why, you ask?

534
00:56:56,660 --> 00:57:00,562
Hello? Hi, sweetheart.

535
00:57:01,198 --> 00:57:03,792
What's the time there?
You're still up?

536
00:57:03,967 --> 00:57:07,198
You should be in bed by now.

537
00:57:07,704 --> 00:57:11,333
Mommy's having lunch
with friends.

538
00:57:11,508 --> 00:57:15,035
It's noisy.
No, you don't know them.

539
00:57:15,212 --> 00:57:18,079
They're all new friends.

540
00:57:20,283 --> 00:57:22,080
You don't know them.

541
00:57:23,120 --> 00:57:28,285
I've been busy playing tennis,
and dancing and hiking too.

542
00:57:29,493 --> 00:57:32,690
Skiing? Sure you can go skiing.

543
00:57:32,863 --> 00:57:37,129
So you won't be back
for Christmas?

544
00:57:37,300 --> 00:57:40,235
No problem, you go skiing.

545
00:57:40,504 --> 00:57:42,404
There will be lots
of parties here.

546
00:57:42,572 --> 00:57:45,837
Maybe I'll go away
with friends.

547
00:57:47,077 --> 00:57:52,379
Sandy, you have to call Daddy.

548
00:57:53,316 --> 00:57:56,581
Mommy misses you.

549
00:57:57,554 --> 00:58:01,115
Okay. Take care. Bye!

550
00:58:02,492 --> 00:58:03,959
Bye!

551
00:58:06,763 --> 00:58:11,791
I want them to be this generation's
new pop idols.

552
00:58:11,968 --> 00:58:14,402
Good for you!

553
00:58:14,571 --> 00:58:16,903
Hello?
I'm in a meeting.

554
00:58:17,074 --> 00:58:20,771
Get on with your practicing, then.
Bye!

555
00:58:21,445 --> 00:58:24,778
See how dedicated they are?

556
00:58:24,948 --> 00:58:28,577
Do you want to book them
for a concert?

557
00:58:31,021 --> 00:58:35,458
''The law is inadequate
in protecting the elderly at home.

558
00:58:36,093 --> 00:58:37,583
Although....''

559
00:58:39,563 --> 00:58:41,793
This is all about...

560
00:58:42,566 --> 00:58:46,866
...the aged.

561
00:58:48,338 --> 00:58:51,136
There is nothing else in here!

562
00:58:55,846 --> 00:58:58,815
Let's not read anymore, okay?

563
00:58:59,683 --> 00:59:01,651
No more news.

564
00:59:02,753 --> 00:59:08,089
How about I trim your nails?

565
00:59:09,059 --> 00:59:11,220
They're really long!

566
00:59:11,728 --> 00:59:15,664
I've got clippers here.
Let me trim your nails.

567
00:59:18,034 --> 00:59:20,502
I used to cut
my daughter's nails.

568
00:59:26,143 --> 00:59:30,671
But one year,
when she turned 1 2...

569
00:59:31,915 --> 00:59:34,281
...she started to do it herself.

570
00:59:35,185 --> 00:59:39,747
She hasn't needed me much
since then.

571
00:59:43,026 --> 00:59:46,826
Children grow up and leave.

572
00:59:48,298 --> 00:59:52,496
Parents age and go away.

573
00:59:55,372 --> 00:59:57,306
Men go away too.

574
01:00:00,911 --> 01:00:02,776
Good thing they do.

575
01:00:04,347 --> 01:00:06,747
Otherwise, I wouldn't
have met you.

576
01:00:11,855 --> 01:00:13,379
Right?

577
01:00:15,392 --> 01:00:18,623
Let's hear it
for the Sunday Sisters.

578
01:00:18,795 --> 01:00:22,026
Next up are Cindy and Candy.

579
01:00:23,333 --> 01:00:25,631
Hey, who are you?

580
01:00:26,469 --> 01:00:29,097
Who invited you?
Why did you sing so many songs?

581
01:00:29,272 --> 01:00:30,933
Who the hell are you?

582
01:00:31,107 --> 01:00:33,302
What's your problem!
You know who I am?

583
01:00:33,476 --> 01:00:36,445
-Who cares? You're an asshole.
-Are you crazy?

584
01:00:36,613 --> 01:00:38,376
Crazy? I'm defending you here.

585
01:00:39,049 --> 01:00:41,244
Why are you so mad?
What's with you?

586
01:00:41,418 --> 01:00:44,012
I defend you, and you yell at me?
You're crazy!

587
01:00:44,187 --> 01:00:47,247
I'm crazy? You never think
of people's feelings.

588
01:00:47,457 --> 01:00:50,426
-I have feelings too!
-Have you finished?

589
01:00:50,594 --> 01:00:52,255
-Stay out of this.
-What is it?

590
01:00:52,462 --> 01:00:53,895
-Stop it!
-Who are you?

591
01:00:54,064 --> 01:00:58,364
-I'm their manager. Talk to me.
-Manager? From where?

592
01:00:58,535 --> 01:01:00,696
We're just starting out.

593
01:01:00,871 --> 01:01:03,499
-That figures.
-Shut up. What's it to you?

594
01:01:03,673 --> 01:01:06,904
-Pipe down.
-Stop it. Quiet, please.

595
01:01:07,077 --> 01:01:08,908
Did I give permission
to go on-stage?

596
01:01:09,079 --> 01:01:11,411
-You're crazy.
-You're nuts.

597
01:01:12,082 --> 01:01:15,279
-Excuse me, what did you say?
-Why didn't you get my permission?

598
01:01:15,452 --> 01:01:18,717
-Why do I need your permission?
-Don't you know who I am?

599
01:01:19,256 --> 01:01:20,951
No!

600
01:01:21,992 --> 01:01:24,552
His dad is the principal.

601
01:01:27,497 --> 01:01:29,488
Get out, you guys. Get out.

602
01:01:29,699 --> 01:01:32,827
-Get out.
-Wait outside.

603
01:01:33,003 --> 01:01:34,664
-Nut case.
-I'm sorry.

604
01:01:34,838 --> 01:01:37,136
-They're an ignorant bunch!
-They're new.

605
01:01:37,307 --> 01:01:40,401
-They were very rude.
-You're right. Damn ignorant.

606
01:01:40,577 --> 01:01:45,981
-And rude.
-Forgive them. I apologize!

607
01:02:06,937 --> 01:02:08,461
Sorry!

608
01:02:11,775 --> 01:02:14,266
We must have been terrible
up there.

609
01:02:14,444 --> 01:02:19,438
No way.
We Sunday Sisters top everyone.

610
01:02:51,982 --> 01:02:54,212
What is the bravest thing
you've done?

611
01:02:54,384 --> 01:02:58,753
-Me? Milking a cow.
-Milking a cow? I'm serious!

612
01:02:58,922 --> 01:03:04,690
That cow kicked someone to death.
No one dared milk her.

613
01:03:05,628 --> 01:03:07,926
So do you dare make love to me?

614
01:03:30,286 --> 01:03:31,810
There's no one here.

615
01:03:34,724 --> 01:03:36,453
It's dirty.

616
01:03:38,928 --> 01:03:40,623
Very dirty.

617
01:03:40,797 --> 01:03:42,628
This one is nicer.

618
01:03:43,533 --> 01:03:46,127
Maybe every stall is different.

619
01:03:48,471 --> 01:03:51,201
What? Why are you laughing?

620
01:03:52,509 --> 01:03:54,841
Why are you laughing?

621
01:03:56,146 --> 01:03:58,580
What's so funny?

622
01:04:55,238 --> 01:04:58,264
What? What?!

623
01:05:06,449 --> 01:05:08,246
Check her out.

624
01:05:12,388 --> 01:05:15,323
It's the girl we met
this morning.

625
01:05:24,000 --> 01:05:25,991
-Hey.
-What do you want?

626
01:05:27,337 --> 01:05:29,931
-Where's your friend?
-Mind your own business!

627
01:05:30,106 --> 01:05:32,040
-Let's call it a truce.
-No.

628
01:05:32,208 --> 01:05:34,472
-Come on.
-No.

629
01:05:34,644 --> 01:05:37,636
You have a pen? A pen.

630
01:05:39,749 --> 01:05:42,650
-What do you want?
-Can I give you my number?

631
01:05:42,819 --> 01:05:47,313
Call me and we'll go out sometime.
Okay?

632
01:05:51,661 --> 01:05:53,925
It's all right. Just a kid.

633
01:05:54,764 --> 01:05:56,732
Don't worry.

634
01:05:57,800 --> 01:05:59,233
May I sit with you?

635
01:06:26,729 --> 01:06:31,632
Put this up for me.
Yes, right up there.

636
01:06:31,935 --> 01:06:35,962
-This side. Put it here.
-Do it yourself!

637
01:06:36,139 --> 01:06:40,974
You're taller. Help me!
Higher up. Thank you.

638
01:06:51,221 --> 01:06:52,586
Xiang!

639
01:06:53,856 --> 01:06:56,689
Listen to me.

640
01:07:01,231 --> 01:07:02,664
Xiang.

641
01:07:16,980 --> 01:07:19,448
Don't act like this.

642
01:07:19,616 --> 01:07:21,379
-Leave me alone!
-No. Xiang!

643
01:07:28,625 --> 01:07:30,149
Be careful!

644
01:07:34,731 --> 01:07:37,063
What's going on?

645
01:07:37,567 --> 01:07:39,694
Come help rescue my fish.

646
01:07:41,204 --> 01:07:42,728
Can you see that one?

647
01:07:43,573 --> 01:07:45,336
You're standing on it!

648
01:07:45,875 --> 01:07:48,036
There's one over there.

649
01:07:48,678 --> 01:07:51,340
Be careful. Don't squash it.

650
01:07:52,148 --> 01:07:53,979
There's another one!

651
01:07:58,421 --> 01:08:01,720
-Give it to me. Qi, give me.
-Be careful.

652
01:08:10,233 --> 01:08:12,224
What are you two doing?

653
01:08:13,569 --> 01:08:15,161
Catch it!

654
01:08:19,776 --> 01:08:22,074
-Hello.
-Who's this guy?

655
01:08:24,147 --> 01:08:27,810
-This is ridiculous.
-How should I know who he is?

656
01:08:27,984 --> 01:08:29,849
Who are you?

657
01:08:30,553 --> 01:08:33,681
-What's it to you?
-What kind of game is this?

658
01:08:33,890 --> 01:08:36,586
-This is too much.
-You have no right to question me.

659
01:08:36,793 --> 01:08:41,890
Nor do you. You think I don't know
what you and May were doing?

660
01:08:42,065 --> 01:08:44,295
-It's all crap.
-May asked for my help.

661
01:08:44,467 --> 01:08:46,367
-I did nothing!
-Of course she asked.

662
01:08:46,536 --> 01:08:49,004
And you do whatever she wants?

663
01:08:49,572 --> 01:08:51,301
Right?

664
01:08:51,507 --> 01:08:54,271
-You have no right to lecture me.
-Don't act like this.

665
01:08:54,444 --> 01:08:55,843
Don't touch me.

666
01:08:56,012 --> 01:09:00,108
I need to get a new fishbowl.
Close the door when you leave.

667
01:09:18,468 --> 01:09:20,766
Who are you?

668
01:09:20,937 --> 01:09:23,633
I'm Situ.
I've come for the piano.

669
01:09:24,240 --> 01:09:29,268
-Sorry, today isn't a good day.
-I can see that. Another time?

670
01:09:38,955 --> 01:09:40,820
<i>I have to stop flying...</i>

671
01:09:42,125 --> 01:09:44,218
<i>...change my numbers...</i>

672
01:09:44,427 --> 01:09:46,327
<i>...and disappear
from this world.</i>

673
01:09:59,308 --> 01:10:01,003
Look over there.

674
01:10:01,177 --> 01:10:04,476
Check out the one in gray.
He's looking over here.

675
01:10:04,647 --> 01:10:06,512
Behave yourself, girl!

676
01:10:06,682 --> 01:10:09,776
I looked at the same man for 30 years.
Now there are new ones.

677
01:10:09,952 --> 01:10:14,013
-Why shouldn't I stare?
-Don't just look, do something.

678
01:10:14,223 --> 01:10:17,192
Go for it, Lily!

679
01:10:18,594 --> 01:10:22,121
-All talk, no action?
-Calm down.

680
01:10:23,866 --> 01:10:26,562
Oh, my God, she's going for it!
She's fearless!

681
01:10:26,736 --> 01:10:28,670
She won't give up!

682
01:10:30,273 --> 01:10:32,264
Yes, here's the sauna.

683
01:10:33,176 --> 01:10:35,235
-Hi.
-Hello.

684
01:10:35,411 --> 01:10:38,812
Excuse me,
I just told my friends...

685
01:10:38,981 --> 01:10:42,075
...we went to primary school together.
They won't believe me!

686
01:10:42,552 --> 01:10:46,545
You probably don't remember
that we were classmates.

687
01:10:46,756 --> 01:10:49,224
You probably don't recall
my name--

688
01:10:49,592 --> 01:10:51,059
Lily Shi.

689
01:10:52,695 --> 01:10:54,492
-What?
-It wasn't primary school.

690
01:10:54,697 --> 01:10:57,757
We were in middle school together.
I was in Ms. Chen's class.

691
01:10:57,934 --> 01:10:59,595
You were in Ms. Liu's class.

692
01:10:59,769 --> 01:11:01,737
No kidding?

693
01:11:02,905 --> 01:11:04,566
Here's my card.

694
01:11:04,807 --> 01:11:08,038
-''Zhang Shi-Jie''?
-Call me Jerry.

695
01:11:12,915 --> 01:11:15,475
Let's meet up sometime.

696
01:11:16,118 --> 01:11:18,052
Miss, can I get a pen?

697
01:11:21,824 --> 01:11:23,621
''Zhang Shi-Jie.''

698
01:11:24,160 --> 01:11:25,957
Zhang Shi-Jie.

699
01:11:34,437 --> 01:11:37,600
Hello. All alone?

700
01:11:38,908 --> 01:11:41,968
You don't have a lunch date?

701
01:11:43,746 --> 01:11:45,873
Take your time.

702
01:11:46,048 --> 01:11:48,448
I meant with your girlfriends.

703
01:11:49,819 --> 01:11:53,915
I was just passing by.
I thought I'd see how you were doing.

704
01:11:57,727 --> 01:12:00,025
The flowers are beautiful as usual.

705
01:12:00,196 --> 01:12:02,790
Maybe I'll buy some.

706
01:12:04,800 --> 01:12:07,098
But there's no one
to give them to.

707
01:12:08,504 --> 01:12:11,735
I came to talk to you
about Sandy.

708
01:12:12,842 --> 01:12:14,639
She still won't talk to me.

709
01:12:14,810 --> 01:12:19,713
Can you put in a word for me?
Please?

710
01:12:20,216 --> 01:12:23,743
This is grown-up business.
Why drag her into this?

711
01:12:24,587 --> 01:12:26,817
I've discussed it with Amy--

712
01:12:27,323 --> 01:12:29,018
Hello? Hold on a second.

713
01:12:29,425 --> 01:12:30,824
Listen to me.

714
01:12:30,993 --> 01:12:34,292
Amy wouldn't ask Sandy
to call her ''Mom.''

715
01:12:34,964 --> 01:12:36,727
So it's okay, right?

716
01:12:36,899 --> 01:12:39,026
Please talk to her.

717
01:12:40,469 --> 01:12:43,165
Hey! Would you--?

718
01:12:43,973 --> 01:12:46,669
Would you please talk to her
about it?

719
01:12:47,543 --> 01:12:49,408
Let's talk some other time.

720
01:12:56,719 --> 01:13:00,211
<i>-Love Home Florist.
-This is Jerry. Is this Lily?</i>

721
01:13:00,323 --> 01:13:04,953
Yes. This is she.
Jerry. Sorry about just now.

722
01:13:05,161 --> 01:13:07,823
<i>I'd like to order some flowers.</i>

723
01:13:08,497 --> 01:13:10,556
Were we really in school together?

724
01:13:10,733 --> 01:13:13,531
Why can't I remember?

725
01:13:14,136 --> 01:13:17,333
<i>I was sort of a nerd back then.
Not the kind people remember.</i>

726
01:13:17,506 --> 01:13:20,270
Me too.
Why do you remember me?

727
01:13:23,012 --> 01:13:25,810
You'd like to order flowers?
What kind?

728
01:13:25,982 --> 01:13:27,950
<i>Can you help me decide?</i>

729
01:13:28,351 --> 01:13:30,376
Who are they for?

730
01:13:30,553 --> 01:13:34,387
Is it a special occasion?

731
01:13:34,624 --> 01:13:36,319
<i>They're for a girl.</i>

732
01:13:36,892 --> 01:13:38,860
<i>The message is, ''Dear Emmy.... ''</i>

733
01:13:39,028 --> 01:13:42,896
<i>E-M-M-Y.
''Welcome back. Love, Jerry. ''</i>

734
01:13:47,203 --> 01:13:49,034
How much do you want to spend?

735
01:13:49,872 --> 01:13:53,205
<i>Your call.
They need to be beautiful and big.</i>

736
01:13:53,476 --> 01:13:55,341
<i>I trust your judgment.</i>

737
01:14:00,883 --> 01:14:04,216
Lily, what exactly
should the card say?

738
01:14:04,387 --> 01:14:08,847
It says here ''Dear Emily''
and ''Go to hell.''

739
01:14:10,726 --> 01:14:12,250
This is....

740
01:14:12,461 --> 01:14:18,024
Should it be ''Dear Emily,
welcome back. Love, Jerry''?

741
01:14:18,701 --> 01:14:21,864
-Okay. Yes.
-Is it ''Emily''?

742
01:14:29,745 --> 01:14:32,145
-Flowers to deliver, Xiang!
-Okay.

743
01:14:51,500 --> 01:14:53,297
-Welcome!
-Lily, l....

744
01:14:53,469 --> 01:14:55,061
Wait a moment.

745
01:14:57,073 --> 01:14:59,906
-I'll add some of this.
-Okay.

746
01:15:00,509 --> 01:15:02,977
-How much?
-1 000 NT. Qin, take the money.

747
01:15:03,145 --> 01:15:04,544
Okay!

748
01:15:04,714 --> 01:15:06,614
Thank you.

749
01:15:09,285 --> 01:15:11,344
Please deliver the flowers
on Friday.

750
01:15:11,520 --> 01:15:13,351
-We will.
-Thanks again.

751
01:15:13,522 --> 01:15:15,012
Take care!

752
01:15:16,726 --> 01:15:19,661
Do you want more flowers?
We've got some good ones today.

753
01:15:19,829 --> 01:15:22,491
Did you like the flowers?
I can do a new arrangement.

754
01:15:22,665 --> 01:15:27,159
-You misspelled the name.
-Misspelled? Misspelled what?

755
01:15:27,336 --> 01:15:30,169
''Emmy.'' You wrote ''Emily.''

756
01:15:30,473 --> 01:15:34,068
Oh, no! Qin, you misspelled it.

757
01:15:34,243 --> 01:15:36,939
-Can't be!
-Check it!

758
01:15:37,113 --> 01:15:39,877
-I'm so sorry.
-Jerry, I really am sorry!

759
01:15:40,049 --> 01:15:43,314
My God, how could this happen?
She must have been upset.

760
01:15:43,486 --> 01:15:45,852
Nothing jewelry can't fix.

761
01:15:47,356 --> 01:15:49,153
Wow. That's nice!

762
01:15:49,358 --> 01:15:51,826
-Women are--
-Easy to please!

763
01:15:51,994 --> 01:15:55,191
One little stone and we're all set.
Men are more difficult.

764
01:15:55,364 --> 01:15:57,491
-Correct it.
-All right.

765
01:15:57,666 --> 01:16:00,157
-Change it to Emily. No, I mean--
-Emmy!

766
01:16:00,269 --> 01:16:01,600
-Emmy.
-Emmy.

767
01:16:01,771 --> 01:16:04,934
-E-M-M-Y.
-E-M-M-Y.

768
01:16:05,107 --> 01:16:06,734
Jerry, I'm sorry.

769
01:16:06,909 --> 01:16:09,673
Let me pay you back.
Really, I must.

770
01:16:09,845 --> 01:16:14,111
-Don't worry.
-Please! Are you free now?

771
01:16:14,283 --> 01:16:18,913
It will be really quick.
Let's just have a quick lunch.

772
01:16:19,088 --> 01:16:22,615
Wait for me. Wait.
I won't take no for an answer.

773
01:16:22,825 --> 01:16:25,020
It'll make me feel better.

774
01:16:25,227 --> 01:16:26,819
I'm so embarrassed!

775
01:16:33,702 --> 01:16:36,364
I haven't had a quiet meal for ages.

776
01:16:37,573 --> 01:16:42,408
<i>Jerry Zhang, 47,
divorced for eight years.</i>

777
01:16:42,578 --> 01:16:45,979
<i>Son's in college. Lives alone.</i>

778
01:16:46,148 --> 01:16:49,049
<i>Girlfriend is young,
a flight attendant.</i>

779
01:16:49,218 --> 01:16:52,915
<i>He's in the toy business
and travels to China a lot.</i>

780
01:16:53,355 --> 01:16:56,813
<i>He might move there,
but she doesn't want to go.</i>

781
01:16:57,026 --> 01:17:00,518
<i>They fight about this a lot.</i>

782
01:17:00,930 --> 01:17:05,026
Jerry, do you play tennis?

783
01:17:06,669 --> 01:17:08,364
Do you like hiking?

784
01:17:10,539 --> 01:17:12,302
I like to stay home.

785
01:17:13,275 --> 01:17:16,005
I like the comfort of home.

786
01:17:21,116 --> 01:17:23,243
-Hello.
-Mrs. Zhao!

787
01:17:23,419 --> 01:17:25,319
It's Miss Shi now.
You forgot again.

788
01:17:25,487 --> 01:17:27,421
-Sorry, Miss Shi.
-Yes.

789
01:17:27,623 --> 01:17:30,683
-Reservation for Friday?
-Friday? Okay.

790
01:17:30,893 --> 01:17:34,124
-7:30.
-7:30. How many of you? Two.

791
01:17:34,296 --> 01:17:36,526
Two. Usual table?

792
01:17:36,699 --> 01:17:39,896
It's not for me.
It's for Mr. Zhang. Jerry Zhang.

793
01:17:40,069 --> 01:17:41,764
Jerry Zhang. Okay. Good.

794
01:17:42,104 --> 01:17:44,095
Should I have a bottle
of wine ready?

795
01:17:45,040 --> 01:17:46,598
Wine?

796
01:17:48,544 --> 01:17:52,241
-Put some champagne on ice.
-Okay.

797
01:18:00,289 --> 01:18:03,690
Welcome!
Do you have a reservation?

798
01:18:03,859 --> 01:18:07,351
-Jerry. Jerry Zhang.
-Yes. This way, please.

799
01:18:14,637 --> 01:18:17,504
Mr. Zhang,
we have champagne for you.

800
01:18:17,873 --> 01:18:19,363
Thanks.

801
01:18:29,985 --> 01:18:32,749
Your guests are here, Miss Shi.

802
01:18:40,095 --> 01:18:44,725
You must be Emmy.
These are for you from Mr. Zhang.

803
01:18:45,534 --> 01:18:47,468
I'm the florist.

804
01:18:47,636 --> 01:18:51,663
I am here to apologize
for misspelling your name.

805
01:18:53,776 --> 01:18:57,542
-No problem. Thank you.
-You two enjoy. Bye!

806
01:19:35,417 --> 01:19:37,408
This way. Into the alley.

807
01:19:42,024 --> 01:19:43,651
Keep going!

808
01:19:50,532 --> 01:19:52,762
Love Home Florist. This is Lily.

809
01:19:52,935 --> 01:19:54,664
<i>Lily.</i>

810
01:19:55,604 --> 01:19:58,505
<i>-Thanks.
-How was the food?</i>

811
01:19:59,408 --> 01:20:00,773
Where do we put the fridge?

812
01:20:00,943 --> 01:20:03,343
-In the kitchen, thanks.
-Okay.

813
01:20:03,712 --> 01:20:05,680
Move up a little. Okay.

814
01:20:05,848 --> 01:20:07,509
This way. This way.

815
01:20:08,417 --> 01:20:10,351
-Miss Ku.
-The washing machine?

816
01:20:11,020 --> 01:20:13,887
-Miss Ku?
-Go through the kitchen...

817
01:20:14,056 --> 01:20:15,455
...onto the balcony.

818
01:20:15,657 --> 01:20:19,616
That's not right, mister.
The drawer is on the right side.

819
01:20:19,828 --> 01:20:23,559
Please nail it in. You have
to take the box off first.

820
01:20:25,000 --> 01:20:28,265
-Where should we put this?
-Move back first.

821
01:20:29,271 --> 01:20:32,434
Don't leave yet.
I need help.

822
01:20:33,075 --> 01:20:35,066
Guys, take the case off outside.

823
01:20:36,211 --> 01:20:37,803
So how about this?

824
01:20:37,980 --> 01:20:41,677
Take the speakers and put it....

825
01:20:41,850 --> 01:20:46,014
-Where should I put this?
-Over here, okay? Right here.

826
01:20:46,255 --> 01:20:50,692
-How's that? Yeah.
-The cabinet? Put it here.

827
01:20:50,859 --> 01:20:53,123
-That room?
-Yes, thanks.

828
01:20:55,564 --> 01:20:59,364
-Sir, please take these boxes out.
-The mirror's in the way here.

829
01:20:59,668 --> 01:21:02,466
-Is it okay if I move it?
-Okay. Thanks.

830
01:21:05,874 --> 01:21:09,867
-Please put it in that room.
-Okay.

831
01:21:14,083 --> 01:21:16,711
-Please take that case outside.
-Okay.

832
01:21:17,453 --> 01:21:18,715
Here's another one.

833
01:21:21,590 --> 01:21:24,115
Take it down.
Don't leave it by the elevator.

834
01:21:25,794 --> 01:21:28,763
The dryer is done.
Want to test it?

835
01:21:28,964 --> 01:21:30,431
Okay.

836
01:21:38,640 --> 01:21:42,474
I heard you used to go to that
restaurant with your husband.

837
01:21:42,911 --> 01:21:44,845
I rarely hear you mention him.

838
01:21:45,013 --> 01:21:47,413
I'm not interested in the past.

839
01:21:50,085 --> 01:21:51,916
Is he a bastard?

840
01:21:52,354 --> 01:21:57,348
It's no one's fault.
We weren't good for each other.

841
01:21:57,559 --> 01:21:59,550
No one's at fault.

842
01:22:01,430 --> 01:22:03,091
Did your girlfriend leave?

843
01:22:03,265 --> 01:22:05,563
She's flying to America this time.

844
01:22:06,969 --> 01:22:08,596
Do you miss her?

845
01:22:10,506 --> 01:22:16,035
I don't know if I miss her
or if I'm just lonely.

846
01:22:17,446 --> 01:22:21,940
People are selfish.
We find a partner to keep us...

847
01:22:22,518 --> 01:22:25,316
...from loneliness in old age.

848
01:22:30,659 --> 01:22:32,786
Where do I put the mirror?

849
01:22:33,061 --> 01:22:35,325
-Here. In the corner.
-There.

850
01:22:37,299 --> 01:22:40,791
Just put it here. Careful.

851
01:22:40,969 --> 01:22:43,494
All right. One, two, three.

852
01:22:45,607 --> 01:22:48,872
That's good. Yeah, over.
There you go.

853
01:22:49,044 --> 01:22:51,274
-Here?
-Okay.

854
01:23:02,224 --> 01:23:04,192
You don't remember me, do you?

855
01:23:15,837 --> 01:23:18,305
My mother gave me this
when I was 8.

856
01:23:19,074 --> 01:23:21,133
I'm a bit reluctant
to give it up.

857
01:23:21,610 --> 01:23:23,373
But keeping it....

858
01:23:26,181 --> 01:23:29,378
You're giving it to your daughter?
And she's also 8?

859
01:23:30,018 --> 01:23:31,747
Why do you want her
to study piano?

860
01:23:31,920 --> 01:23:33,353
Yaqi?

861
01:23:33,755 --> 01:23:36,724
My daughter-- Her mother
passed away two years ago.

862
01:23:37,392 --> 01:23:41,055
I think all little girls like to play piano.

863
01:23:42,731 --> 01:23:48,226
At any rate, I think it's nice
for girls to learn piano.

864
01:23:49,771 --> 01:23:51,500
Have you asked her?

865
01:23:52,941 --> 01:23:54,772
I want to surprise her.

866
01:23:55,277 --> 01:23:58,906
I don't have much money,
and your price fits my budget.

867
01:23:59,314 --> 01:24:00,838
So here I am.

868
01:24:03,318 --> 01:24:07,516
Where's the metronome?

869
01:24:08,857 --> 01:24:10,552
Do you mind its age?

870
01:24:10,759 --> 01:24:12,226
Whose age?

871
01:24:12,427 --> 01:24:16,625
You'll need a new one of these.
I mean the age of the piano.

872
01:24:17,499 --> 01:24:21,094
It's old,
but the sound is excellent.

873
01:24:21,270 --> 01:24:24,535
I haven't been taking care of it.

874
01:24:25,540 --> 01:24:30,773
It needs tuning,
but it's still a good piano.

875
01:24:33,649 --> 01:24:35,947
Sounds like I'm talking
about myself.

876
01:24:37,552 --> 01:24:40,146
Promise me
you'll take care of it.

877
01:24:40,322 --> 01:24:43,052
I've had it for 20 years.

878
01:24:43,258 --> 01:24:46,284
I'm very attached to it.

879
01:24:49,031 --> 01:24:51,625
-These are great dumplings.
-Really good!

880
01:24:52,200 --> 01:24:55,727
Eat one garlic clove
and a dumpling.

881
01:24:55,904 --> 01:24:57,929
One clove for each dumpling!
You sure?

882
01:24:59,007 --> 01:25:01,532
Why not?
I'm sleeping alone tonight.

883
01:25:01,710 --> 01:25:04,838
-What about you?
-Same here.

884
01:25:06,381 --> 01:25:09,350
-Eat up, then.
-Okay.

885
01:25:15,324 --> 01:25:16,814
Good!

886
01:25:21,496 --> 01:25:23,760
Why didn't you order food?

887
01:25:24,599 --> 01:25:26,294
-I've finished.
-Finished?

888
01:25:26,468 --> 01:25:29,869
-Why didn't you wait for us?
-Forget it. I'll order.

889
01:25:30,372 --> 01:25:32,169
You're half an hour late!

890
01:25:32,341 --> 01:25:34,605
I didn't know the movie
was so long.

891
01:25:34,776 --> 01:25:36,767
Jie, 1 0 dumplings for me.

892
01:25:36,945 --> 01:25:41,041
Okay, 1 0 dumplings.
And five more for me.

893
01:25:42,517 --> 01:25:45,213
-Beer.
-She's mad at us.

894
01:25:45,387 --> 01:25:47,446
-Who?
-Her.

895
01:25:47,656 --> 01:25:51,217
Why? Don't be.

896
01:25:51,593 --> 01:25:54,460
Excuse me.
Can I have the chili sauce?

897
01:25:54,629 --> 01:25:56,893
Don't be mad. Here's to you.

898
01:25:57,065 --> 01:25:59,693
-From Jie to Jie.
-Right! You're both Jie.

899
01:25:59,868 --> 01:26:03,497
Yeah. You have a connection
with both of us.

900
01:26:03,672 --> 01:26:05,196
Let's drink.

901
01:26:07,976 --> 01:26:10,536
Just one drink.

902
01:26:10,712 --> 01:26:12,304
I'm leaving.

903
01:26:13,415 --> 01:26:15,246
What happened?

904
01:27:10,305 --> 01:27:13,968
Walking in the Rain

905
01:27:56,384 --> 01:28:00,184
Does the song make you sad?

906
01:28:02,557 --> 01:28:06,857
I don't have time for sadness.
I just try to enjoy it.

907
01:28:58,947 --> 01:29:03,384
<i>Xiang? Where are you?</i>

908
01:29:05,320 --> 01:29:07,618
Don't ever call me again!

909
01:29:34,082 --> 01:29:36,243
-Morning.
-Morning.

910
01:29:41,489 --> 01:29:43,423
What are you doing here?

911
01:29:43,925 --> 01:29:46,917
-This is my block too.
-Oh.

912
01:30:11,419 --> 01:30:14,445
Coming! Coming! Hello?

913
01:30:25,634 --> 01:30:28,194
I got it, Qin.

914
01:30:35,543 --> 01:30:38,341
<i>-Hello?
-Bad day, Lily.</i>

915
01:30:39,414 --> 01:30:44,351
<i>One of my shipments was rejected.
I have to go to China to fix it.</i>

916
01:30:44,519 --> 01:30:48,615
<i>Emmy is having a party,
and I can't go. She's very upset.</i>

917
01:30:48,823 --> 01:30:51,758
This time, don't buy more jewelry.

918
01:30:52,260 --> 01:30:56,697
If a man calls you
once or twice a day...

919
01:30:57,565 --> 01:30:59,590
...what does it mean?

920
01:31:00,568 --> 01:31:05,767
I'm sure he's not interested in me.

921
01:31:06,307 --> 01:31:09,174
But he even calls me
when he's abroad.

922
01:31:14,716 --> 01:31:17,514
Emmy! Going on vacation?

923
01:31:17,686 --> 01:31:19,313
I'm going to Japan.

924
01:31:20,321 --> 01:31:23,757
-How nice!
-To try to work things out.

925
01:31:25,226 --> 01:31:27,126
Don't be temperamental.

926
01:31:31,266 --> 01:31:35,100
He said he was pretty upset.

927
01:31:35,336 --> 01:31:37,201
I asked if he'd quarreled
with Emmy.

928
01:31:37,372 --> 01:31:40,705
He didn't want to discuss it.

929
01:31:40,875 --> 01:31:44,003
He only says
that he's irritated...

930
01:31:44,179 --> 01:31:47,580
...and must make
an important decision.

931
01:31:50,752 --> 01:31:52,686
What do you think it is?

932
01:31:56,825 --> 01:31:59,350
Wow, gorgeous!

933
01:32:34,062 --> 01:32:36,030
I'm so sorry.

934
01:32:37,899 --> 01:32:40,026
Hang on.

935
01:32:50,378 --> 01:32:52,608
You still have
your wedding ring on.

936
01:32:54,716 --> 01:32:57,184
But I've never seen
your family here.

937
01:32:57,552 --> 01:33:01,784
Hey! You're so cute.
Come here!

938
01:33:01,990 --> 01:33:05,391
It's your roommate's birthday today.

939
01:33:05,994 --> 01:33:09,361
Her whole family's here.

940
01:33:10,698 --> 01:33:13,531
I celebrated with my family last year.

941
01:33:16,704 --> 01:33:19,730
But we mustn't be jealous of others.

942
01:33:25,113 --> 01:33:28,014
Hurry, blow out the candles!

943
01:34:11,759 --> 01:34:13,351
What are you doing?

944
01:34:13,561 --> 01:34:15,825
-They want us to pay every week.
-Every week.

945
01:34:15,997 --> 01:34:19,228
-Can I put it on my credit card?
-Yes.

946
01:34:23,972 --> 01:34:26,440
How could my credit card
get denied?

947
01:34:27,876 --> 01:34:30,367
I'll check it out.
Lend me your phone card.

948
01:34:30,812 --> 01:34:32,279
No.

949
01:34:36,718 --> 01:34:40,245
Operator.
I'm calling collect to Hong Kong.

950
01:34:40,488 --> 01:34:42,149
You can keep your card.

951
01:34:42,891 --> 01:34:44,859
I'm broke too.

952
01:34:46,127 --> 01:34:48,857
I'll have my mom
send money here.

953
01:34:50,365 --> 01:34:53,061
What do you mean,
no collect calls?

954
01:34:53,334 --> 01:34:55,461
You call and ask
for Li Mei-ling.

955
01:34:55,637 --> 01:34:57,798
Tell her
that her daughter's calling.

956
01:34:58,339 --> 01:35:00,500
I'm not paying the charges.

957
01:35:00,742 --> 01:35:03,142
Collect call, get it?

958
01:35:04,946 --> 01:35:08,109
You don't know
what a collect call is?

959
01:35:21,095 --> 01:35:23,290
We'd better find Shi Ge.

960
01:35:23,998 --> 01:35:27,399
For what? He lies
and screws people's wives.

961
01:35:27,568 --> 01:35:29,661
That's all he's good for.

962
01:35:30,672 --> 01:35:32,902
Then why did you come here?

963
01:36:22,890 --> 01:36:24,482
Shi Ge.

964
01:36:40,708 --> 01:36:44,906
We have no money
to pay the rent.

965
01:36:54,589 --> 01:36:56,580
You want some?

966
01:37:08,536 --> 01:37:11,096
You really like singing?

967
01:37:14,042 --> 01:37:17,136
I never meant to lie to you.

968
01:37:18,246 --> 01:37:20,544
I wrote a lot of songs.

969
01:37:23,151 --> 01:37:25,711
I worked really hard.

970
01:37:27,321 --> 01:37:31,849
But they don't want them.

971
01:37:33,094 --> 01:37:35,494
They said the songs were crap.

972
01:37:36,030 --> 01:37:41,764
I took them to dinner.
They said the songs were crap.

973
01:37:45,173 --> 01:37:48,609
-This studio's finished.
-Why?

974
01:37:49,544 --> 01:37:52,172
I don't have money for the rent.

975
01:37:52,713 --> 01:37:56,149
We can record a demo.
I can sing--

976
01:37:56,317 --> 01:37:57,682
No way!

977
01:37:57,852 --> 01:38:02,789
Crap! They're all crap!

978
01:38:08,262 --> 01:38:09,820
Sorry.

979
01:38:14,635 --> 01:38:17,627
Take the money and go home.

980
01:38:17,972 --> 01:38:19,906
Good girl.

981
01:38:21,476 --> 01:38:24,809
Just go home.

982
01:38:25,480 --> 01:38:27,209
Don't sing.

983
01:38:30,485 --> 01:38:33,682
Don't cry. Don't sing.

984
01:38:33,955 --> 01:38:37,391
I never even got to record anything...

985
01:38:37,725 --> 01:38:39,989
...and you want me to go home.

986
01:38:45,900 --> 01:38:47,731
Go in.

987
01:38:48,870 --> 01:38:50,804
Go in and sing.

988
01:38:51,939 --> 01:38:53,634
Good girl.

989
01:38:54,342 --> 01:38:56,071
Go inside and sing.

990
01:38:57,345 --> 01:38:59,279
Go on.

991
01:39:41,289 --> 01:39:44,952
<i>I was thinking
about a blue story.</i>

992
01:39:45,159 --> 01:39:47,252
<i>It gave me a wonderful feeling.</i>

993
01:39:47,461 --> 01:39:52,694
<i>When I tell my friends the story,
they always ask, ''And then what?''</i>

994
01:39:52,867 --> 01:39:57,236
<i>I say, ''There is no 'and then. '
The story is over. ''</i>

995
01:39:58,839 --> 01:40:00,966
<i>I'm really homesick.</i>

996
01:40:14,989 --> 01:40:17,355
<i>I'm finally feeling the pain.</i>

997
01:40:19,260 --> 01:40:21,751
<i>Until there's a cure...</i>

998
01:40:22,363 --> 01:40:26,823
<i>...perhaps soap operas
and ice cream...</i>

999
01:40:27,101 --> 01:40:29,001
<i>...will do the trick.</i>

1000
01:40:45,052 --> 01:40:50,388
<i>Mom, I want to settle down,
but how?</i>

1001
01:40:53,461 --> 01:40:56,294
<i>It's easy to find someone
who loves me.</i>

1002
01:40:56,464 --> 01:40:58,955
<i>But where is the right man?</i>

1003
01:41:00,434 --> 01:41:04,131
<i>You always said,
''Men always leave. ''</i>

1004
01:41:04,639 --> 01:41:08,871
<i>So whenever I'm in love,
I'm always suspicious of the man.</i>

1005
01:41:09,176 --> 01:41:12,270
<i>Will I ever be lucky enough
to find true love?</i>

1006
01:41:12,780 --> 01:41:15,044
<i>Is love ever that simple?</i>

1007
01:41:15,483 --> 01:41:20,819
<i>When the right man shows up,
how will I know he's the one?</i>

1008
01:41:22,657 --> 01:41:24,215
<i>Mom...</i>

1009
01:41:25,126 --> 01:41:28,755
<i>...can you at least give me a sign?</i>

